node.text:
Since the founding of the ERAU Spacesuit Utilization of Innovative Technology Laboratory (S.U.I.T. Lab) in 2017, students have completed many exciting projects, including ones that are highlighted in this video made by @spacesuitup!
The lab is a testbed for spacesuit design research where students get to work with industry partners to develop innovative solutions. Visit erau.edu/spacesuit for more information about the team! 🚀👨‍🚀🛰 #spacesuitup

In celebration of #NationalWomensDay, we're recognizing triple alumna Jayde King, who is paving the way for women of color in the Human Factors discipline.

From starting her journey as an Eagle at her South Florida high school to completing her doctorate in August 2020, King is the first Gaetz Aerospace Institute graduate to earn a Ph.D. from Embry-Riddle. 🦅 #GoERAU #HumanFactors

node.text:
Happy #NationalMoonDay! 🌑🚀🧑‍🚀

On July 20, 1969, Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin became the first humans to land on the moon. In this photo from @NASA, taken by Armstrong, Aldrin stands near the leg of the Eagle lunar module during the #Apollo11 moonwalk.
 
Fifty-two years later, there are still many firsts we can achieve. Our eye is on the moon's Oceanus Procellarum, where our CubeSat camera will touchdown right before the Intuitive Machines lunar lander to snap the first image of a spacecraft as it makes an extraterrestrial landing. 📸
 
Beyond the stellar spacecraft selfie, Embry-Riddle will be the first university to land a project on the moon's surface, the first to establish wifi there, and the first to test @nasakennedy’s electrodynamic dust shield to remove lunar regolith from a camera lens! Follow our moon mission @ERAUeaglecam 🦅
 
#NasaArtemis #engineering #MoonMission #ToTheMoon #ERAUtotheMoon #AerospaceEngineering #ComputerEngineering #SoftwareEngineering #ElectricalEngineering #GoERAU #ERAUEngineer

node.text:
A big welcome to aerospace engineer James W. Gregory, Ph.D. who was named as dean of the College of Engineering!

Dr. Gregory, who once led an autonomous drone team that set world speed and distance records, will begin his service with Embry-Riddle by the fall 2021 semester. Currently, he serves as professor and chair of the Department of Mechanical and Aerospace Engineering at The Ohio State University, where he had previously worked as director of the Aerospace Research Center.

To read more, head to the swipe up link in our Stories! 🦅 #GoERAU
